# NPM / npmjs.com
#
# This package is public: anyone can `npm install logs-gateway` with no token.
# A token (or `npm login`) is only needed for maintainers running `npm publish`,
# or for private / scoped packages elsewhere — not for consumers of this repo.
#
# Put your real token in your USER-LEVEL file only (not in this repo):
#   Windows: %USERPROFILE%\.npmrc
#   macOS/Linux: ~/.npmrc
#
# Or run: npm login
#
# Create a token: https://www.npmjs.com/settings/~/tokens
# Then one line (replace YOUR_TOKEN):
#   //registry.npmjs.org/:_authToken=YOUR_TOKEN
#
# Why not commit .npmrc here? GitHub blocks pushes that contain tokens; the
# repo copy must stay out of git. Your local ~/.npmrc is still used by npm.
